Bluetooth: btusb/btmtk: Add MT7902 Bluetooth support

Add USB device ID 13d3:3579 (IMC Networks/Azurewave) and hardware
variant 0x7902 for the MediaTek MT7902 (Wi-Fi 6E) Bluetooth interface
found on the ASUS Vivobook A1404ZA and similar laptops.

Without this patch, the device binds via the generic vendor+interface
match (USB_VENDOR_AND_INTERFACE_INFO 0x13d3) but not as a proper
BTUSB_MEDIATEK device, causing the HCI reset to time out:

  Bluetooth: hci0: Opcode 0x0c03 failed: -110
  Bluetooth: hci0: Unsupported hardware variant (00007902)

The hardware variant 0x7902 is added to the 79xx switch case so that
btmtk_fw_get_filename() generates the firmware path
mediatek/BT_RAM_CODE_MT7902_1_x_hdr.bin and btmtk_setup_firmware_79xx()
performs the standard WMT firmware download. The MT7902 BT firmware
ships with linux-firmware.

The information in /sys/kernel/debug/usb/devices about the Bluetooth
device is listed as the below.

T:  Bus=01 Lev=01 Prnt=01 Port=02 Cnt=01 Dev#=  4 Spd=480  MxCh= 0
D:  Ver= 2.10 Cls=ef(misc ) Sub=02 Prot=01 MxPS=64 #Cfgs=  1
P:  Vendor=13d3 ProdID=3579 Rev= 1.00
S:  Manufacturer=MediaTek Inc.
S:  Product=Wireless_Device
S:  SerialNumber=000000000
C:* #Ifs= 3 Cfg#= 1 Atr=e0 MxPwr=100mA
A:  FirstIf#= 0 IfCount= 3 Cls=e0(wlcon) Sub=01 Prot=01
I:* If#= 0 Alt= 0 #EPs= 3 Cls=e0(wlcon) Sub=01 Prot=01 Driver=btusb
I:* If#= 1 Alt= 0 #EPs= 2 Cls=e0(wlcon) Sub=01 Prot=01 Driver=btusb
I:* If#= 2 Alt= 0 #EPs= 2 Cls=e0(wlcon) Sub=01 Prot=01 Driver=btusb

Link: https://github.com/jetm/mediatek-mt7927-dkms/issues/66
Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>
Tested-by: Dian <prasetyaeckoaldiano@gmail.com>

diff --git a/btusb.c b/btusb.c
--- a/btusb.c
+++ b/btusb.c
@@ -668,6 +668,8 @@
 	{ USB_DEVICE(0x13d3, 0x3576), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
 						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
 	{ USB_DEVICE(0x13d3, 0x3578), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
 						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
+	{ USB_DEVICE(0x13d3, 0x3579), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
+						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
 	{ USB_DEVICE(0x13d3, 0x3583), .driver_info = BTUSB_MEDIATEK |
 						     BTUSB_WIDEBAND_SPEECH },
diff --git a/btmtk.c b/btmtk.c
--- a/btmtk.c
+++ b/btmtk.c
@@ -1371,6 +1371,7 @@
 	case 0x7668:
 		fwname = FIRMWARE_MT7668;
 		break;
+	case 0x7902:
 	case 0x7922:
 	case 0x7925:
 	case 0x7961:
